Kafka Tweet Stream Producer

This project implements a Python Kafka producer that simulates a tweet stream by reading a CSV file and sending messages to a topic at a rate of 10-15 messages per second with updated timestamps.

Services
Kafka broker in KRaft mode
Topic creation helper
Python producer application

How to run
Place the twcs.csv file in the project directory. Use the command docker-compose up --build to start the infrastructure.

How to check application logs
Use the command docker logs -f python_app to see the messages being sent by the producer.

How to check Kafka topic
To check the total number of messages in the topic, use the command docker exec hw8-kafka-1 /bin/kafka-run-class kafka.tools.GetOffsetShell --broker-list localhost:9092 --topic tweets

To read the messages directly from the partition, use the command docker exec -it hw8-kafka-1 /bin/kafka-console-consumer --bootstrap-server localhost:9092 --topic tweets --partition 0 --offset earliest --max-messages 20

Technical details
The producer uses the kafka-python library and connects to the broker via the internal Docker network. Data is serialized in JSON format. The streaming rate is controlled by a 0.07s delay between messages.
